don&#x27;t confuse standard libraries, libraries and languages :)<p>Prelude is functional, C++ STL and the C library are imperative.<p>There is a valid argument that a &#x27;good ol&#x27; fashioned&#x27; bit of procedural code (for loop) makes this same algorithm easier to read than either of these (it certainly makes it shorter), since it tells you explicitly what it is doing rather than assuming (usually a safe assumption) that programmers can understand and trust things like sum, map and take/limit.<p>i&#x27;m thinking of something like:<p><pre><code>  int iTotal = 0;
  for( int i = 0; i < 10; ++i )
  {
      iTotal += i * i;
  }</code></pre>
